title: Census, The Lower 48 state U.S. coastal region population change between 2000 and 2006, USA, 2006
name: Census, The Lower 48 state U.S. coastal region population change between 2000 and 2006, USA, 2006
description:
The poly shapefile is based on Census data that compares Census 2000 population levels to estimates in July, 2006 for all the counties that are designated by NOAA (see the URL below) as "Coastal Region Counties". There are 645 jurisdictions, whose combined population in was over 146.6 million (Year 2000) and estimated to be 154.3 million in 2006. In both years, the largest and the smallest counties were Los Angeles, CA and Kenedy, TX. Flagler, FL registered the largest percent change (66.7%) and St. Bernard, LA registered the highest percent decrease (-76.9%). The later is direct result of the 2005 Katrina disaster.   

http://www.census.gov/geo/landview/lv6help/coastal_cty.pdf

author.source: Bureau of Census, U.S. Commerce Dept
